# API Contracts

Source of truth: `server/src/routes/`. Update server route + `apiEndpoints.js` + matching `*Api.js` / hook in one change.

## Routes

| Method | Path | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| GET | `/api/blog/all` | Published blogs |
| GET | `/api/blog/:blogId` | Blog detail |
| POST | `/api/blog/add-comment` | `{ blog, name, content }` |
| POST | `/api/blog/comments` | `{ blogId }` |
| POST | `/api/blog/add` | multipart: `blog` JSON + `image` |
| POST | `/api/blog/delete` | `{ id }` |
| POST | `/api/blog/publish` / `/unpublish` | `{ id }` |
| POST | `/api/blog/generate` | `{ prompt }` |
| POST | `/api/admin/login` | `{ email, password }` |
| GET | `/api/admin/dashboard` | not `/stats` |
| GET | `/api/admin/blogs` / `/comments` | |
| POST | `/api/admin/approve-comment` / `/unapprove-comment` / `/delete-comment` | `{ id }` |
| GET | `/uploads/blogs/:filename` | Static images |

## Response

```javascript
{ success: true, count?, blogs?, comments?, message?, token? }
{ success: false, message: string }
```

## Do Not

- Use PUT/DELETE on client without a matching server route
- Change an endpoint on one side only
